@node "Introduction" "Introduction"

                       AMIGA CHATLINE ORGANIZATION @{FG fill}@{fg shine}
                             Version 1.2
                      (HTML version included..SOON!)

                     Hello Amiga lovers everywhere !


           If you have been on the chatlines, you certainly know how
    worthless they are at the present time. Sure, if you want to sit on
    your multi-thousand dollar computers and waste your valuable time
    without hardly ever learning a thing, YOU most certainly disagree !
    BUT, there are some of us Amiga owners who love the superiority of
    the great AMIGA computer, and have gone onto the chat channels to
    LEARN ! The AMIGA CHATLINE ORGANIZATION is for this group of people.

                           PURPOSE:

         The AMIGA CHATLINE ORGANIZATION is committed to setting forth
    useful ideas to help us all get the most out of our time on IRC
    chatlines.These include:

    1) in-depth knowledge of IRC programs
    2) rules of behaviour while online
    3) uniform standards for kicks,bans,akicks,OPs,SOPs,& sound filenames
    4) complete knowledge of IRC commands
    5) new servers, new channels, and AMIGA CHATLINE events,
       and more...................


        WHY YOU SHOULD BE INTERESTED IN The AMIGA CHATLINE ORGANIZATION:

    1) BECAUSE YOU WANT TO GET THE MOST OUT OF YOUR TIME ON YOUR AMIGA
       COMPUTER
    2) BECAUSE YOU WANT TO GET THE MOST OUT OF YOUR TIME ONLINE

    3) IF YOU ARE TIRED OF THE ASSHOLES ON THE CHATLINES, WHO BELIEVE IT IS
       RIGHT TO KICK PEOPLE OUT OF CHANNELS "for fun", ATTACK AND INSULT
       YOUR FAMILY,and ALL OTHER FORMS OF ABUSE AND MISCHIEF.

    
@endnode

@node A.C.O.STANDARDSFORKICKS "A.C.O. Standards for Kicks"



                 A.C.O. Standards for Kicks,Bans, & Akicks

    --LISTEN UP !

          YOU SHOULD ONLY KICK, or GET KICKED FROM A CHANNEL FOR:

    1) FOR FLOODING ANYONE.... FLOODING IS A CONSTANT STREAM OF TEXT TO
        HARRASS, ANNOY, OR NUETRALIZE ANOTHER USER

    2) For making violent threats and insisting that YOU are serious about
        carrying them out !

    3) For insulting someone's family members ...AT ALL
    4) For repeatedly insulting any user, in the MAIN channel window


    4) For repeatedly insulting the Great Amiga computer..

    5) For coming on an Amiga channel, using any computer EXCEPT AMIGAs
        note: Most of us have found that non-amiga users cannot relate
        to the Amiga, due to it's tremendous superiority over EVERY other
        platform known; except SGI(cost-$25,000 minimum) If you find a rare
        exception to this, then, fine.

           YOU SHOULD ONLY BAN, or GET BANNED FROM A CHANNEL FOR:

    1) Repeating the above mentioned things that would get you kicked !

        YOU SHOULD ONLY AKICK, or GET KICKED FROM A CHANNEL FOR:

    1) Repeatedly doing the above mentioned things that would get you banned

     Otherwise.. total freedom of speech is the rule. You may argue,chat, or
     come to learn. I have only learned 1 single time on the chatline.

@endnode

@node A.C.O.STANDARDSFORSOUNDFILES "A.C.O. Standards for Sound files"
                         A.C.O. Standards for SOUND FILES

              NECCESSITY FOR HAVING UNIFORM SOUND FILENAMES:
     Unless BOTH, the sender And reciver of a sound file have the file being
     sent, no sound is heard or played ! Also,THE SOUND FILENAMES HAVE TO BE
     THE SAME IN ORDER FOR ANY SOUND TO BE PLAYED OR HEARD. Yes, ye special
     breed of computer lovers..the need for a sound filename standard is
     desperately needed !
        SOUND filename standards are in progress NOW..BUT we need YOUR
     help. Send us your favorite sounds. Send no more than 5 files. 4 files
     must be LESS THAN 100K...1 may be over 100K, but LESS THAN 200K. WE,in
     turn will a)listen to all files b)decide best name for files c)pack
     sound files into an lha archive(s) d)send all donators regular archives
     e)files will be freely distributable f)files will be amiga snd,iff,8svx

     Please NOTE: All sounds submitted which violate ©Copyright laws, must
     and will be deleted.....as if I should have to tell you cool AMIGANS !


@endnode
@node SOMEHELPFULHINTS "Some HELPFUL HINTS"

                             Some HELPFUL HINTS:

     1) Using AmIRC gives you the superiority over any situation

     2) lag and netsplits are cut to a minimun under these conditions
        a)when users are connected to the SAME name server
        b)when using a Direct Client Connection or DCC

     3) DalNet, Galaxynet, and Cobra are the best IRC networks.
        Undernet.org, unfortuantely, is a broken down network.

     4) You don't deserve to be kicked off a channel without a real reason

     5) Avoid assholes restricting your access and banning you because you're
        smarter than these violent dummies. I have talked with alot of these
        people, and they refuse to stop attacking people. So, forget these
        assholes, and come to AMIGA channels, to learn without being attacked.

     6) The ONLY way to have complete control, while on the chatlines, is
        to FOUND your own channel...and BTW..never point your anger or insults
        at a channel FOUNDER..(you may NOT get back onto that channel again,
        if you do !) The FOUNDER alone, has the power to akick (permanently
        ban you)

     7) An IRC channel is really a "communication station". Once connected,
        there are many forms of communication possible; from typing text into
        the main window, /msg people, send chanserv memos, sending/receiving
        files, or holding computer training classes.


             You can find a COMPLETE list of DALNET IRC commands at:

                   http://www.inet-direct.com/cooksey/clchg.htm

@endnode

@node OTHERAMIGATHINGSOFINTEREST "OTHER AMIGA THINGS OF INTEREST"

                      OTHER AMIGA THINGS OF INTEREST:

      1) If you don't already know-- Aminet is NOT Public Domain !
         Aminet is the private collection of ONE man-Urban Mueller. He can
         end Aminet any time HE chooses. If you want YOUR program to have
         a future, contact us for arangements to register and/or sell YOUR
         program from our web site(s) ! We welcome programs that Urban has
         banned from Aminet.@{"Offer to ALL Amiga PD authors" link OFFERTOALLAMIGAPDAUTHORS}
                           ....And, thanks needs to be given to Urban for
         the great job he and others have done in providing so many of us
         with an organized, regular supply of free "publicly accessible"
         Amiga software. Thanks Urban, Matthias, Shane....

      2) Send any donations of cash, equipment, software, hardware, or
         otherwise..to

                        AMIGA CHATLINE ORGANIZATION
                        c/o Terry Cooksey
                        P.O. Box 586
                        Jonesboro, AR 72403

         *Please tell us YOUR ideas as to how to spend YOUR cash donations*

       3) Send comments, or any ideas for improving chatlines, and/or
          advancing the Amiga, Amiga software, or the AMIGA CHATLINE
          ORGANIZATION...

                    to: terry@inet-direct.com
                     or terry@insolwwb.net


           TELL EVERYONE --IT'S TIME TO LEARN ON THE CHATLINES--FINALLY


     A great thanks to my friend --Stone, from Sweden. I learned more in 2
     hours with Stone, than all my time previously spent on the chatlines.

@endnode
@node OFFERTOALLAMIGAPDAUTHORS "Offer to ALL Amiga PD authors"
@{FG shine}This is to Amiga PD software authors:@{FG text}

     I am turning my personal web site(s) into commercial web site(s). I
 would like to promote Amiga PD software. Direct sales for a registered
 version; or download the unregistered one free. My plan is to organize
 MANY PD software programs into a one-stop amiga PD software store on the
 Internet. I do not have all the details "written in stone", so I would
 certainly agree to most any idea that you would have. I want the program
 authors themselves, to have complete direct control over their programs.
 If you have NOT visited my web site(s), please do so now. I am able to
 give proof of my integrity, and ability to carry out this task. It is
 the free programs that hve kept my amiga going. Over the past few years,
 I have seen that the AMIGA can soar higher than ever. The big companies
 bailed out of amiga-dom, and you guys kept on with your programs; and
 believing in the Amiga. I try to promote your programs as much as I can
 but, I have NOT been authorized by any of you to do so. SASG does a
 small impression of what my idea is. One unique value that I possess,
 is that I am in the central United States. I could take mail orders
 from within the U.S.; though I believe the real bulk of orders for
 your programs can be placed from a web page form. The terms are your's
 to make; so please understand that I am ready to act within days, and
 do know what I am trying to accomplish here. Your idea could be to
 just put a part of your present page on my site. I believe in freedom
 personally. So, I would never want to be a part of binding you to any
 terms of mine. Your programs might suffer from the antagonism. I hope
 to register more programs this year. I learned to direct my software
 dollars to PD stuff. I did this because the commercial software had
 no chance of being upgraded. Thanks for your amiga programs !!!
     I do hope to hear from you...

                           Sincerely..Your fellow Amigans,

                               Terry & Sandra Cooksey

  VISIT Our SITE(S).....there are 75+ pages..and they mirror one another..

  http://www.insolwwb.net/~terry/
  http://www.inet-direct.com/cooksey

^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
Please pass this onto to the authors of any Amiga programs, you may know.
